- Implementation of the Singleton pattern in JavaScript to manage the theme state (e.g., light or dark mode).
- Varied page content (e.g., headers, paragraphs, lists, and a table) to demonstrate how the theme affects the entire page.
- A discussion section at the bottom of the page that explains the pros and cons of the Singleton pattern, as well as when alternatives like Dependency Injection might be more appropriate.

