Below is a complete, self-contained HTML file that demonstrates a dark and light theme toggle using the Singleton pattern for state management. The Singleton pattern is implemented in JavaScript to ensure there's only one instance managing the theme state across the page. This allows the theme to be applied consistently to multiple varied elements, such as headings, paragraphs, buttons, and a custom content div.

